    <div id="About" class="text_block">
		<h2 id="About_title" class="text_title"> About </h2>
			<p>Glitchy Cyborg is the front end for my personal hobby "super" computer, Gaea.
			Calling it a supercomputer is of course a joke, but you get the idea. 
			The curent plan being, build this front end, and give people a chance to 
			try MPI on ARM based hobby clusters without having to build one themselves. </p>

			<p>I'm making it available to others for a couple reason, mostly learning purposes.
			Please keep in mind, I'm no expert, just passionately curious.</p>

			<p>I'm also considering setting up a forum, where can people can talk about their 
			own projects, get help, post reviews, watever. We'll see. </p>

			<p>Of course, this is all very fluid, things can change, not tied to anything </p>

			<p>Cheers!</p>
			<p>DPGraham4401</p>
	</div>
	
    <div id="Tech_Specs" class="text_block">
		<h2 id="Tech_Specs_Title" class="text_title"> Tech Specs </h2>
        <p>Gaea consist of a 5 <a href="https://www.pine64.org/devices/
        single-board-computers/rock64/">Rock64</a> single board computers from Pine64
        Like most SOCs, the ROCK64 uses ARM cores which use a reduced Instruction (RISC)
        and are considered more power efficient than their CISC counteparts</p>
        <h3>Rock64 v2 specs </h3>
        <figure>
            <img src="Assets/Pictures/ROCK64_600x355.jpg" alt="photgraph of Rock64" />
            <br/>
            <figcaption> Image taken from Pine64.org </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <ul id="specs">
            <li>Rockchip RK3328 CPU</li>
            <ul id="RK3328">
                <li> quad core</li> 
                <li> A53 ARM cores</li>
                <li> 64 bit</li>
            </ul>
            <li>2 Gb DDR3 RAM</li>
            <li> 32 Gb emmc storage</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The cluster uses a Beowolf architecture (1 login node, 4 slave nodes)
        with 64 Gb of steady state scratch storage. Additional info on other Pin64 products can be found at
        <a href="www.pine64.org">Pine64.org</a></p>
	</div>
	
